---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="AI Integration Consulting | Richard Kappel" description="Custom AI systems that give your team back the hours buried in busywork. Quoting, scheduling, customer follow-up, data entry. Book a free automation audit.">

  <!-- 1. HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50/60 via-white to-white -z-10"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[800px] h-[600px] bg-brand-500/[0.04] rounded-full blur-3xl -z-10"></div>
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-24 md:pt-32 pb-20">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="animate-fade-in">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-600 mb-5">AI Integration Consulting</p>
          <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-[1.1] text-slate-900">
            What would you do with 16 extra hours every week?
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            Use it to finally open that second location. Be home for dinner instead of doing quotes at 9pm. Triple your pipeline without hiring a single person.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            Those hours are already in your business. Buried under work that doesn't need a human. I find them and give them back.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-3.5 bg-brand-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-brand-700 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-brand-200 transition-all duration-200">
              Find Your 16 Hours
            </a>
            <a href="#how-it-works" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-3.5 text-slate-500 font-medium hover:text-brand-600 transition-colors duration-200">
              See How It Works ↓
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-in-right">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
            <img src="/hero-animation.svg" alt="16 hours reclaimed every week" class="w-full max-w-[420px]" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. THE FEAR — COMPETITIVE PRESSURE -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-slate-50/70">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-14 slide-in-up">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-600 mb-3">Competitive Pressure</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">Your competitors aren't waiting.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="slide-in-left space-y-5 text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            While you're reading this, someone in your market already has this running.
          </p>
          <p>
            They're responding to leads in 90 seconds while you check voicemail at lunch. They're sending quotes from the truck while you do them at the kitchen table at 9pm. They're not smarter. They're not bigger. They automated first.
          </p>
          <p>
            Every week you wait, the gap gets wider. Not by a little. By the compound effect of speed, consistency, and follow-through.
          </p>
          <p>
            This isn't about keeping up with technology. It's about keeping up with the business down the street that figured this out six months ago.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 pt-2 border-l-[3px] border-brand-500 pl-5">
            The question isn't whether AI changes your industry. It's whether you're the one using it or the one losing to it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-in-right">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center p-4">
            <img src="/hourglass-time.svg" alt="Time slipping away — the hours you lose don't come back" class="w-full max-w-[280px]" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. THE EMPOWERMENT ANCHOR -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="slide-in-up text-center mb-10">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-600 mb-3">Philosophy</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 leading-tight">
          This isn't about cutting your team.<br class="hidden md:block" /> It's about unleashing them.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="slide-in-up space-y-5 text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed" style="animation-delay: 0.15s">
        <p>
          Let's be clear. I don't build these tools to take anyone's job. I build them to take over the part of the job nobody wanted in the first place.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your best salesperson shouldn't be copying data into spreadsheets. Your office manager shouldn't spend three hours a day on emails that all say the same thing. Your field team shouldn't be doing paperwork at 9pm.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you remove the busywork, something happens. People get creative. They build relationships. They solve problems. They do the work they were actually hired to do.
        </p>
        <p>
          A 3-person team with the output of 10. Not because they work harder. Because they finally have the time to work on what matters.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 pt-4">
          Better tools make better teams. That's the whole philosophy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. PAIN MATH — WHERE THE HOURS ARE HIDING -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-slate-50/70">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-14 slide-in-up">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-600 mb-3">The Math</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">16 hours didn't disappear. Here's where they went.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="slide-in-up stat-card bg-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-layered border border-slate-100 hover:shadow-layered-lg hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300 text-center">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-center gap-1">
            <span class="font-mono text-5xl font-bold tabular-nums text-brand-600">$4,200</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-base text-slate-400">/mo</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 w-10 h-[2px] bg-brand-500 mx-auto"></div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">What manual admin costs a 5-person team. Every month. That's $50,400 a year buried in work that should take minutes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-in-up stat-card bg-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-layered border border-slate-100 hover:shadow-layered-lg hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300 text-center" style="animation-delay: 0.1s">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-center gap-1.5">
            <span class="font-mono text-5xl font-bold tabular-nums text-brand-600">23</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-base text-slate-400">min</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 w-10 h-[2px] bg-brand-500 mx-auto"></div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">To refocus after one interruption. Your best people get pulled out of real work 31 times a day. For tasks that follow a pattern.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-in-up stat-card bg-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-layered border border-slate-100 hover:shadow-layered-lg hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300 text-center" style="animation-delay: 0.2s">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-center gap-1.5">
            <span class="font-mono text-5xl font-bold tabular-nums text-amber-500">67</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-base text-slate-400">% choose first</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 w-10 h-[2px] bg-amber-400 mx-auto"></div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Of customers choose the first business that responds. Every hour your team spends on admin is an hour a faster competitor is winning the deal.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto slide-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.3s">
        <p class="text-slate-500 text-lg leading-relaxed text-center">
          These hours aren't gone. They're trapped in pattern work. Same emails. Same quotes. Same follow-ups that should have gone out yesterday. Free them first, and the advantage compounds. Wait, and you fall behind.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. WHAT YOU GET — EDITORIAL NUMBERED LIST -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-14 slide-in-up">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-600 mb-3">What I Build</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">What I build for you.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-slate-500 text-lg">Every system is built for your workflows, your data, your business. Nothing off the shelf.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-0 slide-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.1s">
        <!-- Service 1 -->
        <div class="service-item group border-t border-slate-200 py-8 grid md:grid-cols-[4rem_1fr_auto] gap-4 md:gap-8 items-start hover:bg-slate-50/50 -mx-4 px-4 md:-mx-8 md:px-8 transition-colors duration-200 rounded-lg">
          <span class="font-mono text-sm text-slate-300 pt-1">01</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-brand-600 transition-colors">Quote from the job site. Be home by 5.</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Voice notes and photos in. Branded, line-item quotes out. What used to take 45 minutes now takes 5. The kitchen table at 9pm is over.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-brand-600 bg-brand-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full whitespace-nowrap self-start">$3,000 value</span>
        </div>
        <!-- Service 2 -->
        <div class="service-item group border-t border-slate-200 py-8 grid md:grid-cols-[4rem_1fr_auto] gap-4 md:gap-8 items-start hover:bg-slate-50/50 -mx-4 px-4 md:-mx-8 md:px-8 transition-colors duration-200 rounded-lg">
          <span class="font-mono text-sm text-slate-300 pt-1">02</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-brand-600 transition-colors">Every lead gets a reply in under 2 minutes. Even at 2am.</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Smart routing sends hot leads to the right person. Follow-up sequences run on autopilot. No lead falls through the cracks. No deal lost to a slow reply.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-brand-600 bg-brand-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full whitespace-nowrap self-start">$2,500 value</span>
        </div>
        <!-- Service 3 -->
        <div class="service-item group border-t border-slate-200 py-8 grid md:grid-cols-[4rem_1fr_auto] gap-4 md:gap-8 items-start hover:bg-slate-50/50 -mx-4 px-4 md:-mx-8 md:px-8 transition-colors duration-200 rounded-lg">
          <span class="font-mono text-sm text-slate-300 pt-1">03</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-brand-600 transition-colors">Leads book themselves. Your team shows up prepared.</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">New leads get qualified, booked, and prepped without a single email chain. Calendar sync. Automatic reminders. The back-and-forth is gone.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-brand-600 bg-brand-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full whitespace-nowrap self-start">$2,000 value</span>
        </div>
        <!-- Service 4 -->
        <div class="service-item group border-t border-slate-200 py-8 grid md:grid-cols-[4rem_1fr_auto] gap-4 md:gap-8 items-start hover:bg-slate-50/50 -mx-4 px-4 md:-mx-8 md:px-8 transition-colors duration-200 rounded-lg border-b">
          <span class="font-mono text-sm text-slate-300 pt-1">04</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 group-hover:text-brand-600 transition-colors">Reports build themselves. Data entry disappears.</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Photos, forms, emails, documents. Extracted, organized, delivered where your team needs it. Weekly reports generated automatically. Your team reviews, not compiles.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-brand-600 bg-brand-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full whitespace-nowrap self-start">$1,500 value</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center mt-10 slide-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.3s">
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Total value: <span class="font-mono text-brand-600">$9,000+</span> per engagement</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-slate-500">Most businesses need 2 to 3 of these. We start with the one that gives you the most time back.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. BEFORE / AFTER -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-slate-50/70">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 slide-in-up">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-600 mb-3">Results</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">What changes in 30 days.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_auto_1fr] gap-4 md:gap-0 items-stretch slide-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.15s">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-red-100 shadow-layered relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-300 to-red-400"></div>
          <p class="text-red-500 font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">Before</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { label: 'Quote turnaround', val: '45 minutes' },
              { label: 'Lead response', val: 'Hours or next day' },
              { label: 'Admin time', val: '16+ hrs/week' },
              { label: 'Missed follow-ups', val: 'Weekly' },
              { label: 'Team capacity', val: 'Maxed out' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-slate-100 pb-3">
                <span class="text-slate-500 text-sm">{row.label}</span>
                <span class="text-slate-900 font-medium text-sm font-mono">{row.val}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Arrow -->
        <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center px-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shadow-lg shadow-brand-200">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-green-100 shadow-layered relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-400 to-emerald-500"></div>
          <p class="text-green-600 font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">After</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { label: 'Quote turnaround', val: 'Under 5 minutes' },
              { label: 'Lead response', val: 'Under 2 minutes' },
              { label: 'Admin time', val: '2 hrs/week' },
              { label: 'Missed follow-ups', val: 'Zero' },
              { label: 'Team capacity', val: '3x output, same headcount' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-slate-100 pb-3">
                <span class="text-slate-500 text-sm">{row.label}</span>
                <span class="text-green-700 font-semibold text-sm font-mono">{row.val}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-center text-slate-700 text-lg font-semibold mt-10 slide-in-up" style="animation-delay: 0.3s">That's <span class="font-mono text-brand-600">14 hours a week</span>. Back in your hands.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 7. HOW IT WORKS -->
  <section id="how-it-works" class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16 slide-in-up">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-600 mb-3">Process</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">Live in 2 weeks. Not 6 months.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-slate-500 text-lg">No IT department required. No software to learn. No disruption.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <!-- Left: Steps -->
        <div class="space-y-0">
          {[
            {
              step: '01',
              title: 'Free Automation Audit (30 min)',
              desc: 'Walk me through your week. I\'ll find the 2 to 3 workflows eating the most time and money. You leave knowing exactly what to automate first and how many hours come back. Even if we never work together.',
            },
            {
              step: '02',
              title: 'I Build It (1 to 2 weeks)',
              desc: 'Custom AI system built around your specific processes. Your pricing, your templates, your workflows. Not a generic tool with 200 features you won\'t use.',
            },
            {
              step: '03',
              title: 'You Test It On Real Work',
              desc: 'I hand it over. You and your team run it on live jobs. I adjust until it matches exactly how you operate. Nothing launches until you\'re confident.',
            },
            {
              step: '04',
              title: 'It Runs. You Get Your Time Back.',
              desc: 'The system handles the pattern work. Your team focuses on what matters. Revenue capacity goes up. You decide what to do with the hours.',
            },
          ].map((item, i) => (
            <div class={`slide-in-left py-6 ${i < 3 ? 'border-b border-slate-100' : ''}`} style={`animation-delay: ${i * 0.1}s`}>
              <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
                <span class="font-mono text-xs text-brand-500 pt-1.5 shrink-0">{item.step}</span>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-slate-900">{item.title}</h3>
                  <p class="mt-1.5 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <!-- Right: Code block -->
        <div class="slide-in-right">
          <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-layered-lg overflow-hidden">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-400/80"></div>
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-amber-400/80"></div>
              <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-400/80"></div>
              <span class="ml-2 font-mono text-[11px] text-slate-500">quote-agent.py</span>
            </div>
            <pre class="font-mono text-[13px] leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto"><code><span class="text-slate-500"># Your quote agent — built for your workflow</span>
<span class="text-purple-400">from</span> <span class="text-blue-300">agent</span> <span class="text-purple-400">import</span> <span class="text-blue-300">QuoteAgent</span>

<span class="text-slate-300">agent</span> <span class="text-slate-500">=</span> <span class="text-blue-300">QuoteAgent</span><span class="text-slate-400">(</span>
    <span class="text-amber-300">pricing</span><span class="text-slate-500">=</span><span class="text-green-300">"your_rates.csv"</span><span class="text-slate-400">,</span>
    <span class="text-amber-300">template</span><span class="text-slate-500">=</span><span class="text-green-300">"branded_quote.pdf"</span><span class="text-slate-400">,</span>
    <span class="text-amber-300">voice_input</span><span class="text-slate-500">=</span><span class="text-orange-300">True</span><span class="text-slate-400">,</span>
    <span class="text-amber-300">auto_followup</span><span class="text-slate-500">=</span><span class="text-orange-300">True</span>
<span class="text-slate-400">)</span>

<span class="text-slate-500"># Voice note from job site → branded quote</span>
<span class="text-slate-300">quote</span> <span class="text-slate-500">=</span> <span class="text-slate-300">agent</span><span class="text-slate-400">.</span><span class="text-blue-300">generate</span><span class="text-slate-400">(</span>
    <span class="text-amber-300">input</span><span class="text-slate-500">=</span><span class="text-green-300">"voice_note_0472.m4a"</span><span class="text-slate-400">,</span>
    <span class="text-amber-300">photos</span><span class="text-slate-500">=</span><span class="text-slate-400">[</span><span class="text-green-300">"site_1.jpg"</span><span class="text-slate-400">,</span> <span class="text-green-300">"site_2.jpg"</span><span class="text-slate-400">]</span>
<span class="text-slate-400">)</span>

<span class="text-slate-300">quote</span><span class="text-slate-400">.</span><span class="text-blue-300">send_to_client</span><span class="text-slate-400">()</span>  <span class="text-slate-500"># 4 min, not 45</span></code></pre>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-center text-xs text-slate-400 font-mono">Built for your business. Not a generic SaaS.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 8. PROOF / CREDIBILITY -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-slate-50/70">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 slide-in-up">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-brand-600 mb-3">Credibility</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">Built by someone who ships.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="slide-in-left space-y-5 text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>I don't talk about AI. I build with it. Every day.</p>
          <p>I shipped a full SaaS platform in weeks. No development team. No contractors. AI and 20 years of knowing how businesses actually run.</p>
          <p>I run Build to Own Club, a community of founders building their own AI tools. Every edge case, every workaround, every win gets fed back into every system I build.</p>
          <p>20 years building companies across 11 countries. I understand margins, workflows, and customers before I touch any technology.</p>
          <div class="pt-4 border-t border-slate-200 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono text-xs text-slate-500 bg-white border border-slate-200 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">20 Years in Business</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-xs text-slate-500 bg-white border border-slate-200 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">11 Countries</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-xs text-slate-500 bg-white border border-slate-200 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">100+ Builders Community</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-in-right">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl overflow-hidden min-h-[300px]">
            <img src="/richard-kappel.jpg" alt="Richard Kappel" class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-2xl" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 9. WHO THIS IS NOT FOR -->
  <section class="py-20">
